column5: I have been up there a couple of times  this year and I haven't found a bait shop on the way. Coming form Markham
Innisfil Bait And Tackle 5460 Yonge, Bradford, ON L3Z 2A5 Telephone : 905-778-8669    http://www.yellowpages.ca/bus/Ontario/Brad...p;le=83097fe75a   map on link
it's 11.5km north of Bradford/the river  I don't know of any places nearer
That's about 15min north drive past bradford, they didn't have any last friday when I came down.
you guys are the best Thanks very much

From what I've heard the tackle shops are out of smaller shiners, some have bigger shiners, but the gas station on the 400 should have some but may be out of the way. Call ahead to make sure they gotem.
Chuck if this weather keeps up you aint fishing anywhere!
Just think Terry. You could make big bucks in the minna trapp,n .
I feal like the pie piper,follow me up the hwy and ya get all the small minnows ya want.  Sure hope yer all fishing from shore.

Your right about that FF69... Sunday looks a little better +10 degrees and sunny. I might go down to one of the spots around Bluffers and fish from shore  with some worms. Take my Ultra-Ultra light rig and   practice on suckers or catfish.
Harry's in Keswick has small minnows.  I dropped in there on Thursday.
TKS Rover  I can go that way as well
nice mug shot-reminds me of the old Gong Show..the Unknown Comic lives!
